    thinking: "**Analyzing Site Structure**\n\nI\'ve outlined the core components of the site\'s structure. It starts with an announcement bar, followed by navigation, a hero section, and key sections detailing the company\'s mission, work, services, and growth packages. It\'s a typical structure, but understanding the order is important to focus on the key components.\n\n\n**Revising Key Sections**\n\nI\'ve replaced \"Awards\" with \"Why brands choose us\" and shifted \"Just went live with\" to \"What can go live for your brand next\". I also swapped \"Partnerships\" with \"Our Stack\" and \"Testimonials\" with \"What working with us feels like\". This ensures a more compelling narrative flow. I\'m moving on to structuring the project, starting with App.tsx and setting up a components folder for organization. Finally, I\'m leaning toward a premium dark theme or a sleek black/white minimalist theme, based on the bold typography and large font style of \"schbang.com\". I\'m planning to use Space Grotesk for the font, and Framer Motion for smooth animations.\n\n\n**Considering Utility Functions**\n\nI\'m evaluating the need for `clsx` and `tailwind-merge` as utility functions. While I could use template literals, these might offer cleaner class mixing. I\'ll create `lib/utils.ts` and install them provisionally. The page structure is next. I\'ll include the following components from the previous summary: `TopStrip`, `Navbar`, `Hero`, `Manifesto`, `LatestWork`, `Services`, `Packages`, `Proof`, `NextSteps`, `Stack`, `Experience`, and `Footer`, starting with `App.tsx`.\n\n\n**Refining Visual Style**\n\nI\'ve decided to move forward with a dark theme, using `bg-[#0a0a0a] text-zinc-50]` for a premium aesthetic. It aligns well with the \"Brand Brick Studio\" brand. I\'m focusing on the component structure, starting with `TopStrip.tsx`, which will contain the text \"Built for Growth. Designed for Results. One Team. Everything Your Brand Needs. | Start Your Brand Upgrade\".\n\n\n**Defining Navbar Links**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the `Navbar` component, listing out links to crucial sections like \"Our Work\", \"Creative Services,\" and \"Contact\". I\'m also considering the hero section content, aiming for a strong headline like \"One Team. Everything Your Brand Needs.\" or \"Creative. Content. Code. Growth \342\200\224 All Under One Roof.\". I\'ll also add a trust strip with \"3+ Years of Experience | 50+ Brands Served | 9+ Team Members | 12 Core Services\". Finally, I\'ll combine the  `WhatDefinesUs.tsx` and `Manifesto.tsx` components.\n\n\n"
