ng the CTA Emoji**\n\nI\'m now implementing the rocket emoji after \"Start Your Brand Upgrade\" in `TopStrip.tsx` to match the design. I\'ve chosen the lucide `<Rocket />` icon and adjusted the CTA style. I\'m focusing now on the navbar edit.\n\n\\n\\n\n\n**Finalizing the Navbar Component**\n\nI\'m now integrating the final logo and text into `Navbar.tsx`, adjusting the layout. I\'ve added the updated SVG paths. I\'ve checked the updated font styles. I\'m making sure it matches the updated screenshot. I\'m now ensuring the layout is good.\n\n\n**Implementing the Navbar Font**\n\nI\'m now implementing the correct font, as requested. I\'ll make the brand font `Inter`, since that looks right from the image, using `font-sans font-bold` for \"Brand Brick,\" with \"Brand\" as a regular weight and \"Brick\" bold and red. Now I\'ll add the styles into the `Navbar.tsx` component.\n\n\n**Updating the Footer Branding**\n\nI\'m now implementing the same \"Brand Brick\" text style in `Footer.tsx` as in the navbar, with \"Brand\" normal and \"Brick\" bold. This ensures consistent branding across the site, using the same font weight. I\'m focusing on ensuring it looks right.\n\n\n**Adjusting the Layout**\n\nI\'m now integrating the navbar logo and \"Brand Brick\" text, while checking the screenshot (the 2nd image). It must be laid out beside each other, and I\'ll edit the navbar\'s layout. I need to get the layout of \"Brand Brick\" and the navigation to be accurate.\n\n\n**Refining the Top Strip**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the top strip design. I\'ve successfully added the rocket emoji and now I\'m making sure `TopStrip.tsx` perfectly mirrors the image, including the text color, font, and spacing between elements. The current text and emoji will soon be replaced, following a careful layout check.\n\n\n**Implementing the Top Strip**\n\nI\'m now integrating the top strip content based on the provided code and the user\'s latest screenshot. I\'m focusing on text, styling, and the em