  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing Custom Cursor**\n\nI\'m working on a custom cursor component now, and I\'ve decided to render the SVG logo as a moving cursor that follows the user\'s mouse. The plan is to hide the standard cursor and replace it with this animated version of our brick logo. This will definitely make the UI a lot more engaging.\n\n\n**Implementing React Component**\n\nI\'ve begun implementing the `CustomCursor` React component. I am tracking the mouse position using `useState` and listening to `mousemove` events, setting the mouse position in state to update the cursor position. I am also handling `mouseover` events to detect hovers over links and buttons, updating `isHovering` state to change the cursor appearance. This is a solid start.\n\n\n**Refining Cursor Implementation**\n\nI\'m now employing `motion.div` from `framer-motion` for smoother cursor animations. I\'m dynamically updating its `x`, `y`, `scale`, and `rotate` based on mouse position and hover states. I\'ve used spring transitions to add a bit of bounce and realism. The SVG logo renders at 32x32px and is styled with a brand color and drop-shadow, making sure the brick logo is clearly visible, even with the mix-blend.\n\n\n**Addressing Cursor Visibility**\n\nI\'ve tackled the visibility issue. I\'ve updated the component to handle cursor reappearance over iframes. Now, I will just ensure the cursor\'s appearance is correct, even if its color is not. I\'ve also refactored the component to be imported and rendered in `App.tsx`, and I\'ve started the implementation, including logic to handle mouse movement and hover states, and I have just started the `useEffect` hook.\n\n\n**Finalizing Event Handlers**\n\nI\'ve just finished implementing the event handlers within the `useEffect` hook. I\'m listening for `mousemove` to update the cursor position, and I\'ve also implemented `mouseover` to check if the target is a link or button, setting `isHovering` accordingly. I also handle `mouseleave` and `mouseenter` to manage visibility. Now the events are properly managed.\n\n\n**Refining Cursor Logic**\n\nI\'m now focusing on mobile compatibility; I\'m returning `null` if the user is on a touch device, as requested. I\'ve also implemented `useEffect` to manage event listeners for `mouseenter` and `mouseleave`, which are properly removed when the component unmounts or `isVisible` changes to prevent memory leaks and ensure the cursor is properly handled. I\'m satisfied now with the handling of edge cases.\n\n\n**Integrating Custom Cursor**\n\nI\'ve integrated the custom cursor component into `App.tsx`, and it\'s now functional. The brick logo is rendering as intended, replacing the default cursor. I\'ve configured it to track the mouse position, and scale/rotate on hover. The drop shadow is making it clearly visible, and it properly disappears on touch devices. I\'m satisfied.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 21
      nanos: 976440471
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
