is confusing. I need to determine if it refers to the button or the icons within. Further, I have to ensure the \"See Our Services\" styling aligns. The \"red colour tab anna chahiye\" detail is also important.\n\n\n**Interpreting Specificity**\n\nI\'m now clarifying the user\'s explicit intent, particularly surrounding the \"icon\" reference. It appears to refer to *buttons*, not necessarily just icons. The user wants the outlined style until hover, when the button fills red and blinks. I also have to ensure the original buttons keep the \"See Our Services\" styling.\n\n\n**Modifying Visual Style**\n\nI\'m now implementing the style changes for the primary buttons. I\'ve located the navbar button in `Navbar.tsx` and modified the class names to achieve the outlined style by default with a red fill on hover. I\'m focusing on ensuring consistency with other buttons across the application. I will now look for other instances of primary buttons to adapt the provided class names.\n\n\n**Adapting Component Styles**\n\nI\'m now modifying the mobile menu button in `Navbar.tsx` to match the intended styling. I\'ve switched the background to transparent with a border, and added a hover effect with a red fill and shadow. I\'m also addressing the \"Book a Free Strategy Call\" button in `Hero.tsx`, updating it with the same outlined style and hover transition. I\'ll maintain consistency with other elements.\n\n\n**Updating Button Styles**\n\nI\'m now adapting the visual styles for other button components. I\'m focusing on the \"See What We Can Build\" button within `LatestWork.tsx`. I\'ve applied the outlined styling, mirroring the recent changes, and also addressed buttons inside the `Packages.tsx` component to keep the consistent visual theme. I\'ll continue to identify and modify further instances.\n\n\n**Refining Button States**\n\nI\'m now revising my approach to ensure a visual match for all button variants. I\'ve updated the \"Popular\" package button to use a transparent