e switched the animation implementation over to defining the blink keyframes in `index.css` directly, with an easing function for a subtle change, and ensuring consistency across components. I\'m focusing on simplicity and maintainability here.\n\n\n\n**Verifying Implementation Details**\n\nI\'m now focusing on verifying the custom animation implementation. I\'ve opted for a raw CSS `@keyframes` block within `index.css` to define the blinking animation, ensuring precise control. I\'m prioritizing direct CSS for brevity and will test to ensure this is correctly overriding the icon\'s color on hover. I\'ll test the `animate-blink-red` class.\n\n\n**Refining Animation Classes**\n\nI\'m now revising my animation approach to align more closely with the initial description. I was thinking of using `animate-pulse` at first, but decided to implement a custom CSS keyframe block directly within `index.css` for the desired blinking effect. I can apply this using `.hover-blink`. I\'ve added a global `.icon-blink` class to apply the blink effect on hover.\n\n\n**Finalizing Animation Style**\n\nI\'m now completing the hover animation implementation and clarifying the approach. The original step-end animation produced a sharp \"blink\" that fits perfectly. I\'m focusing on defining this behaviour through a custom `@keyframes` animation block within `index.css`. This utilizes a `step-end` timing function, guaranteeing consistency. I will verify that the class, `hover-blink-red`, is properly applied.\n\n\n\n**Implementing Final Effects**\n\nI\'m now finalizing the implementation of the icon hover effects, focusing on clean code. I\'ve switched from arbitrary variants to standard CSS in `index.css`. The blink animation is now implemented through `@keyframes` to control the opacity. I am setting it up as a `group-hover` and `hover` class. I\'ve prioritized the look, by opting for a smoother pulse effect via `ease-in-out` animation.\n\n\n\n**Finalizing Icon Blinking**\n\nI\'m now implementing the red blink animation using the CSS keyframes defined earlier. I\'ve applied the `.icon-blink` class to the appropriate elements across components like `Navbar`, `Hero`, `LatestWork`, `Packages`, `Services`, `NextSteps`, `TopStrip`, and `Footer`. I\'m verifying consistency across all buttons and icons to ensure the desired visual effect.\n\n\n**Refining Button States**\n\nI\'m now focusing on refining the primary button styles. I\'m updating the CSS classes to align with the \"See Our Services\" style until hover, then a red fill and shadow. I\'m going to update `index.css` to add a specific `hover-blink-red` class for a precise effect. I am considering this for implementation across the app.\n\n\n"
